description: The index is comprised of twenty-five of the largest companies, based on market capitalization, that have completed a business combination transaction with a SPAC. The fund will invest in (1) U.S. government securities, such as bills, notes and bonds issued by the U.S. Treasury; (2) money market funds; and/or (3) corporate debt securities, such as commercial paper and other short-term unsecured promissory notes issued by businesses that are rated investment grade or of comparable quality. It is non-diversified.
name: AXS Short De-SPAC Daily ETF
